16: MAGNIFYING OF A LINE INTO LAYERS
The initial line must have all edges in the same sens.
In the normal direction to edges, a quadrangulation of NBCOLI(>0)
layers is done around.
All of layers have a small thickness EPCOLI to represent boundary layers
Then, NBDECO other layers are quadrangulated with a thickness which varies
linearly from EPCOLI to EPDECO.
Attention:
If the normals cross each others, the quadrangulation may be INCORRECT!...
and the quadrangulation must be restricted in a vicinity of the line.
The 2 thickness must have the same sign.
If the thickness EPCOLI is negative, the layers are made on the other
side of the initial line.
